--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
DID THE GATE ENGAGE ON SOL?   ** YES -- the gate engaged. **
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
THE LINCHPIN, RESOLVED (and it is the OPPOSITE of the trap the brief flagged):

There are TWO DBs with a spot/strike column, written by two DIFFERENT code paths:

  * polymarket.db  = the LIVE TRADER's DB (run_multi, db_path="polymarket.db").
    live.py:508  spot_fn = (lambda s=sym: fetch_spot(s)) if (sym and fetch_spot) ...
    -> per-coin spot fetched for EVERY coin (sym = SOLUSDT for sol).
    SOL spot/strike coverage in polymarket.db this hour = 3217/3217 ticks = 100%.
    e.g. R32 spot~73.2 strike~73.15. This is the feed the chop gate reads (tick.spot).

  * market_data.db = the passive MONITOR's DB (record_multi, db_path="market_data.db").
    live.py:605  spot_fn = fetch_spot if is_btc else None
    -> BTC-ONLY spot; sol/eth/xrp recorded as 0 BY DESIGN in the monitor DB.
    SOL spot in market_data.db = 0/3221 (and 0.0% across ALL 641 sol markets, all-time;
    eth 0%, xrp 0%, btc 99.8%).

The brief tentatively designated market_data.db as the gate's source and warned that
SOL spot=0 there would mean "gate NOT engaging." That market_data.db zero is REAL but
it is a recording artifact of the monitor sleeve (is_btc gate at line 605), NOT the
trading path. The gate runs inside the trader, on the trader's tick, sourced from
polymarket.db's per-coin feed -- where SOL spot is fully present. So there is NO
per-coin spot coverage gap on the trading path. The gate engaged on SOL.

Gate code (strategies.py:58-67), for reference -- it no-ops only when spot/strike<=0:
    if self.chop_min <= 0.0 or tick.spot <= 0.0 or tick.strike <= 0.0: return True
    return abs(tick.spot - tick.strike)/tick.strike >= self.chop_min
Since SOL tick.spot was non-zero (polymarket.db), this branch evaluated the real
preabsmove on every SOL round -- it did NOT fall through to the no-op.

GATE BEHAVIOR THIS HOUR (per-round, chop_min ~0.00056):
  - 10/12 fired rounds: preabsmove at entry ranged 0.00095 - 0.00261, all >= 0.00056
    -> gate PASS (legitimate conviction move present). 100% of fired rounds had a real,
    above-threshold directional move. The gate was not rubber-stamping flat rounds.
  - 2/12 (R34, R35): no in-band/gate entry -> correctly skipped. R34 settled NO vs an
    up-strike, R35 settled NO -- the gate/band sat these out as intended.
  Per-coin SOL spot coverage the gate could act on this hour: 12/12 rounds (100%).

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
REVERSAL PATTERN
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
All 4 losses are post-entry REVERSALS -- the underlying moved with conviction in the
bought direction (clearing the gate honestly on round-open->entry data), then reversed
by settle. This is the chop gate's by-design blind spot (it only sees open->entry, never
post-entry), identical to btc h20.

Per loss round (dir@entry = spot-vs-strike the gate cleared on; move entry->settle):
  R33 bought NO  | dir@entry -0.00203 (down, cleared)  | entry->settle +0.00231 (UP)   REVERSAL
  R37 bought NO  | dir@entry -0.00151 (down, cleared)  | entry->settle +0.00386 (UP)   REVERSAL
  R39 bought NO  | dir@entry -0.00219 (down, cleared)  | entry->settle +0.00452 (UP)   REVERSAL
  R42 bought YES | dir@entry +0.00247 (up,   cleared)  | entry->settle -0.00164 (DOWN) REVERSAL
Every loss = direction at entry is OPPOSITE the move to settle. Not one was a flat
round the gate should have skipped -- each had a real, above-threshold move that then
reversed. Winners, by contrast, held direction (e.g. R43 dir +0.00205 -> +0.00778).

INDEPENDENT BINANCE SOLUSDT 1m CONFIRMATION (box reaches Binance klines fine):
  R33 14:05->14:10 opened 73.76, fell to 73.01 intra-round (-1.0%), then chopped back
      up toward strike by settle -- the bot caught the down leg (NO), price recovered.
  R37 14:25->14:30 +0.4%, R39 14:35->14:40 +0.2% choppy up after an early dip,
  R42 14:50->14:55 ran +1.0% up (bot was YES) but the Polymarket settle landed NO 73.07
      vs strike 73.01 -- a near coin-flip settle on a marginal move.
SOL was in a chop/whipsaw regime this hour: 73.0-73.8 oscillation, repeated direction
flips within 5-min windows -- exactly the regime that defeats a momentum-confirmation
gate via reversal, not via the flat-round failure mode.

