--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
vs NORMAL
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
SOL all-time fav_hold fired: 438 rounds, 364 wins = 83.1% win.
This hour: 6/10 = 60%.
One-tailed binomial P(X<=6 | n=10, p=0.831) = 0.073  (p=0.84 -> 0.061).
Unusual-ish but does NOT clear the 0.05 bar. Across many coin-hours per day, a 6/10
SOL hour at p~0.07 is expected to surface regularly -- textbook variance, not a regime
break. Loss magnitudes (~-$23 each) are consistent with the ~$25/trade notional and a
clean favorite-against settle (no oversized/fat-finger loss).

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
ACTION
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1. KEEP THE GATE. 2nd post-deploy outlier, and like btc h20 it is a clean reversal
   cluster, not a gate failure. Two clean post-deploy reversals strengthen the
   "keep the gate, it's variance" conclusion.
2. NO per-coin spot coverage bug on the trading path. The market_data.db SOL spot=0 is
   a known monitor-side artifact (record_multi is_btc gate, live.py:605) and is
   irrelevant to live trading. (Optional, non-urgent cosmetic: flip line 605 to fetch
   per-coin spot so the monitor DB matches the trader DB and future audits aren't
   misled by the 0s -- but this changes NOTHING about trading or the gate.)
3. The reversal blind spot is inherent to an open->entry momentum gate and is the price
   of the edge; do not try to "fix" it with a post-entry reversal stop without separate
   validation -- a stop_p already exists (reversal exit) and these still lost, meaning
   the reversals completed faster than the stop could protect on a 5-min window.
4. Continue monitoring: only escalate to SIGNAL if SOL strings multiple sub-70% hours
   or if losses stop being reversals (i.e. start being flat rounds the gate let through).

